<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-26T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-26T13:00:00-05:00" n="112" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d112">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1140/6: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-26T13:00:00-05:00">November 26, 1918—1 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1864. Your 2380, November 19th. Strictly confidential, for your own
                            information. President and Secretary of State are planning to <pb facs="0212" n="142" xml:id="pg_142"/> sail for France about December
                            4th. The President has made no arrangements for visiting Italy but may
                            do so before his return to the United States.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>